      <title>Leaf Litter Moisture Content at Harvard Forest HEM and LPH Towers 2006</title>
      <creator>
         <individualName>
            <givenName>Julian</givenName>
            <surName>Hadley</surName>
         </individualName>
      </creator>
      <pubDate>2009</pubDate>
      <abstract>
         <section>
            <para>Leaf litter was collected at the time of soil respiration measurements and its moisture content was measured in order to determine the contribution of leaf litter decomposition to measurements of total soil respiration including the litter layer.  Leaf litter moisture has been shown to strongly affect CO2 release from organic soil layers (Borken et al. 2003).</para>
         </section>
      </abstract>
