      <methods>
         <methodStep>
            <description>
               <section>
                  <para>Ten leaves from the uppermost layer of leaf litter were collected at each location where soil respiration was measured.  The leaves were immediately placed into a tightly closed plastic bag, and at the end of the day they were weighed.  They were then dried at 70 degrees C for two days and reweighed.  Leaf moisture content was then calculated as a percentage of the dry weight for each sample.</para>
               </section>
            </description>
         </methodStep>
      </methods>
